Document: Noise
Path: godot/classes/class_noise.rst
Summary: Provides methods for generating 1D, 2D, and 3D noise values, as well as generating images from noise data.

Method: get_image(width: int, height: int, invert: bool = false, in_3d_space: bool = false, normalize: bool = true) → Image
Returns an Image containing 2D noise values.
Note: With normalize set to false, the default implementation expects the noise generator to return values in the range -1.0 to 1.0.

Method: get_image_3d(width: int, height: int, depth: int, invert: bool = false, normalize: bool = true) → Array[Image]
Returns an Array of Images containing 3D noise values for use with ImageTexture3D.create().
Note: With normalize set to false, the default implementation expects the noise generator to return values in the range -1.0 to 1.0.

Method: get_noise_1d(x: float) → float
Returns the 1D noise value at the given (x) coordinate.

Method: get_noise_2d(x: float, y: float) → float
Returns the 2D noise value at the given position.

Method: get_noise_2dv(v: Vector2) → float
Returns the 2D noise value at the given position.

Method: get_noise_3d(x: float, y: float, z: float) → float
Returns the 3D noise value at the given position.

Method: get_noise_3dv(v: Vector3) → float
Returns the 3D noise value at the given position.

Method: get_seamless_image(width: int, height: int, invert: bool = false, in_3d_space: bool = false, skirt: float = 0.1, normalize: bool = true) → Image
Returns an Image containing seamless 2D noise values.
Note: With normalize set to false, the default implementation expects the noise generator to return values in the range -1.0 to 1.0.

Method: get_seamless_image_3d(width: int, height: int, depth: int, invert: bool = false, skirt: float = 0.1, normalize: bool = true) → Array[Image]
Returns an Array of Images containing seamless 3D noise values for use with ImageTexture3D.create().
Note: With normalize set to false, the default implementation expects the noise generator to return values in the range -1.0 to 1.0.